# Recipe from Rebecca Katz book

# Ingredients
* 2 cups brown rice grains, uncooked
* 1 can coconut milk, ~15.5 oz
* ginger, either fresh 1" length chopped, or ~5 dried slices
* 1/2 tsp sea salt
* 2 tsp lime juice, preferably freshly squeezed

# Instructions
* 1. Place brown rice grains in rice cooker and rinse with water.
* 2. Add coconut milk, ginger, salt and lime.
* 3. Top off with water if needed to reach 2 cup mark.
* 4. Set rice cooker to brown rice setting and cook.
